import warnings; warnings.simplefilter('ignore')
from plotnine import *
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import glob
import os

currentFeaturedTableFiles = glob.glob('./CurrentFeaturedHistoryTables/*.json')
latest_Table = max(currentFeaturedTableFiles, key=os.path.getctime)

currentFeatured = pd.read_json(latest_Table)
AllTimeFeatured = pd.read_json("./SpotifyFeaturedMaster.json")

print(ggplot(currentFeatured, aes("Popularity", fill = 'factor(playlist_name)')) 
      + geom_histogram(bins = 20)
     + guides(fill=guide_legend(title="Playlist")))

print(ggplot(currentFeatured, aes(x = ("factor(playlist_name)"), y = "Popularity")) 
      + geom_boxplot()
     + xlab("Playlist")
     + ylab("Popularity")
     + theme(axis_text_x=element_text(rotation=60)))

print(ggplot(currentFeatured, aes(x = ("factor(playlist_name)"), y = "track_positive_sentiment")) 
      + geom_boxplot()
     + xlab("Playlist")
     + ylab("Positive Sentiment")
    + theme(axis_text_x=element_text(rotation=60)))

print(ggplot(currentFeatured, aes(x = ("factor(playlist_name)"), y = "Danceability")) 
      + geom_boxplot()
     + xlab("Playlist")
     + ylab("Danceability")
      + theme(axis_text_x=element_text(rotation=60)))
